etween the observed pulsation periods of variable\nstars and the periods predicted by appropriate theoretical models. The\nasteroseismological techniques allow us to infer details of the internal\nchemical stratification, the total mass, and even the stellar rotation profile.\nIn this review, we first revise the evolutionary channels currently accepted\nthat lead to the formation of white-dwarf stars, and then, we give a detailed\naccount of the different sub-types of pulsating white dwarfs known so far,\nemphasizing the recent observational and theoretical advancements in the study\nof these fascinating variable stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Jun 2019 23:09:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-11"}
